post_text:
From PES

We are excited to see our students back at school on Monday, August 17th. Our buses will run at their normal time and our car rider drop off will open at 7:20. We understand that the first day of school is an important event that families want to share together. For the safety of all PES families, we are limiting the number of visitors on campus by staggering the times parents can walk their children to the classroom. If you wish to walk your child to his/her classroom, we ask that you follow the schedule below.

Grades 2-6 from 7:20 to 8:00
1st grade from 8:00 to 8:30
Kindergarten from 8:30 to 9:00
Pre-K from 9:00 to 9:30

All students will have access to a grab and go breakfast. This schedule is For Monday only. Starting Tuesday, regular bus and car rider schedules will apply, and parents may not visit the classroom.

Thank you for your cooperation. We look forward to a great year.

post_text: Attention ALL Philadelphia High School students entering grades 7-12 for the 2020-2021 academic year: We need each student to complete a course selection form for the upcoming academic year. Please go to our district website www.phillytornadoes.com and click on the 'Family Resources' tab then click on the 'Student Documents' link. Select the appropriate choice form for the grade your child is entering. You may either print the form and fill it out and return it to the PHS office OR complete the form digitally and email to forms@phillytornadoes.com. If you are unable to access the form at our website you may pick up a form at either the high school or middle school office Monday-Thursday 7:30 a.m.-3:30 p.m. Forms are due by Thursday, July 2, 2020.

Meridian Community College is with Lori Oas and Sonia Budhraja.
May 11 at 12:57 PM ¬∑

FREE ONLINE TEACHING COURSE FOR K-12 TEACHERS: Meridian Community College is excited to offer all Mississippi K-12 teachers a free Digital Teaching and Learning course for the summer term (June 1- July 24). This 8-week course will explore online teaching tips and best practice use of Google Classrooms, Canvas, Zoom, and Microsoft Teams, and review computer concepts, including Microsoft applications such as Word, PowerPoint and Excel. This course is offered FREE for ALL Mississippi K-12 teachers! You will want to hurry - register and apply by May 29, 2020!

For teachers interested in Continuing Education Units - this class offers 4.5 CEU's - if interested the cost is $15 for the CEU certification. For more information visit meridiancc.edu/k12free, or call Dr. Marie Roberts at 601.553.3440 or email elearning@meridiancc.edu. #freeclass #makesummercount #findyourwings

PHILADELPHIA PUBLIC SCHOOL DISTRICT DIGITAL LEARNING FAMILY READINESS SURVEY

As school closures continue and as the state develops plans to direct resources to the areas of greatest need, the Mississippi Department of Education is asking each family, in the Philadelphia Public School District, to complete this brief survey. This data will be shared with State Representatives and the Governor to determine the greatest areas of need.

The survey questions address ability of families to connect their children to digital learning offerings from their school through the internet.
